Cell.Text: We left to help with the war and these filth bags swooped in and seized the place. My family is in there.
[S] G|I wish we could offer more help, but our last attack went sour and we're all that is left. | Good luck.
G|Fine then. The blood of my family is on your hands as well as Brurid's.

Node.Caption: dunTrevasWatchQSTGoodbye: I don't have time for this.

Cell.Text: Finally, reinforcements have arrived. | I was expecting more though, you'd better be good.

Cell.Text: G|He's a rogue mage who defected at the beginning of the war. I turned him in but apparently he escaped and now this.

Node.Caption: dunTrevasWatchQuestRunningTopic: Brurid?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Anyway, here is your reward. Thanks again.
[S] Thank you for your help. Did you see my family inside?
G|Hopefully they made it to safety before the attack. I'll begin the search after a quick restock.

Node.Caption: dunTrevasWatchFamilyNotSeenQST: No I didn't see them in there.

Cell.Text: Good, the place is crawling with bandits. We lost some good men trying to take it earlier.
I suspect Brurid planned this, there's been bad blood between us since the king's death. | But to invade my home, kidnap my family...
You ask a lot of questions for a mercenary. Just get in there and open the gate, we'll try and provide help once that's done.

Node.Caption: dunTrevasWatchQSTBadBlood: Sounds like more then just "bad blood".

Cell.Text: The front gate is locked so you'll need to use the mine entrance behind us. Open the front gate and we'll try and give you some support.
My family is everything to me. Clear the fort and on top of the posted reward you can have whatever items you'd like.

Node.Caption: dunTrevasWatchQSTRewardHelp: What can I expect in return for my help?
